  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nI think grouping the extension access control contracts would be more readable and organized, as it happens with the token standard contracts. \r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n### Current structure: \r\n```\r\ncontracts   \r\n‚îÇ\r\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ access\r\n    ‚îÇ   AccessControl.sol\r\n    ‚îÇ   AccessControlCrossChain.sol     \"Extension contract\"\r\n    ‚îÇ   AccessControlEnumerable.sol    \"Extension contract\"\r\n    ‚îÇ   IAccessControlEnumerable.sol   \"Extension contract interface\"\r\n    ‚îÇ   ...\r\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected structure: \r\n```\r\ncontracts   \r\n‚îÇ\r\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ access\r\n     ‚îÇ\r\n     ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ extensions\r\n     ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ   AccessControlCrossChain.sol     \"Extension contract\"\r\n     ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ   AccessControlEnumerable.sol    \"Extension contract\"\r\n     ‚îÇ    ‚îÇ   IAccessControlEnumerable.sol   \"Extension contract interface\"\r\n     ‚îÇ    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\r\n     ‚îÇ   AccessControl.sol\r\n     ‚îÇ   ...\r\n     ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!-- Make sure that you have reviewed the OpenZeppelin Contracts Contributor Guidelines. -->\r\n<!-- https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md -->\r\n",
